body:
Here is the problematic Verilog file `test.v`:
```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps
module gymhnulbvj (in5, clock_10, clock_12, out18);

input wire [23:22] in5;
wire [29:1] wire_4;
reg reg_35;
output wire out18;
input wire clock_10;
input wire clock_12;

assign wire_4 = ~(in5[22:22]);
assign out18 = reg_35 ? 0 : !(!(~((wire_4[6:5] | 8'hc6))));
always @(posedge clock_10 or posedge clock_12) begin
  if (clock_12) begin
    reg_35 <= 0;
  end else begin
    reg_35 <= wire_4;
  end
end
endmodule
```

And here is the testbench file `tb.v` that reveals the issue:
```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps
module testbench;

  reg [23:22] in5;
  reg clock_10 = 0;
  reg clock_12 = 0;
  wire out18;

  gymhnulbvj uut (
    .in5(in5),
    .clock_10(clock_10),
    .clock_12(clock_12),
    .out18(out18)
  );

  initial begin
    $display("Time\tin5\tclock_10\tclock_12\tout18");
    $monitor("%0t\t%d\t%d\t\t%d\t\t%d", $time, in5, clock_10, clock_12, out18);

    in5 = 2'b00;
    #5 clock_12 = 1;  
    #5 clock_12 = 0;

    #5 clock_10 = 1;
    #5 clock_10 = 0;

    #10 $finish;
  end

endmodule
```

In the design `test.v`, the `out18` port is declared as a **1-bit wide wire**. However, the testbench prints a value for `out18` that exceeds the range of a 1-bit wire, specifically showing values like 255 and 254:
```
Time    in5     clock_10        clock_12        out18
0       0       0               0               255
5000    0       0               1               255
10000   0       0               0               255
15000   0       1               0               255
15000   0       1               0               254
20000   0       0               0               254
- tb.v:27: Verilog $finish
- S i m u l a t i o n   R e p o r t: Verilator 5.035 devel
- Verilator: $finish at 30ns; walltime 0.030 s; speed 543.366 ns/s
- Verilator: cpu 0.055 s on 1 threads; alloced 14681163 MB
```

The issue can be reproduced using the following command:
```bash
verilator --binary -Wno-lint --timing test_new.v tb.v
./obj_dir/Vtest
```

### System Details:
- **Verilator version**: Verilator 5.035 devel rev UNKNOWN.REV  
- **OS**: Ubuntu 22.04.5 LTS (Jammy)  
- **Release**: 22.04

